ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION MEASURES

BCSS is committed to public safety, employee safety, continued reliable operation, and regulatory compliance.  Based on this commitment, the Plant Manager has overall responsibility for the development and implementation of the Risk Management Program.  A management system has been developed with clearly defined accountability and responsibility for the Risk Management Program.

To help ensure that any serious chemical releases do not occur, BCSS maintains a release prevention program which is focused on protecting the public and plant employees from hazads associated with an accident or release involving ammonia.  This multifaceted program includes the use of:

Ammonia gas detection and alarms to rapidly alert operators to any problems;

Process instrumentation and interlocks which will shutdown the system and isolate ammonia supplies to the plant if process conditions (such as flow, temperature, and pressure) are not within their appropriate safe operating ranges;

Process safety information which documents the safe design of the process system;

Process hazards analysis to evaluate the chemical and process hazards and make recommendations for safety improvements;

Written operating procedures to ensure the system is operated safely;

Maintenance, inspection, and testing of system components to ensure that they are safe for continued use;

